@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}WELCOME TO JTE's MAGICWB ICONS 9@{ub}

 Well, well, what do we have here, then? More MagicWB icons from @{"JTE" LINK "Address"}?
 Who's icons has he stole now? Everybodys!! 8)

 I hope you folks like these cut'n paste icons from me, it's over 40
 of them, I haven't counted!! It's not Roman Patzner quality, but...

 I was supposed to release this package before christmas, but due to
 laziness and a faulty machine it got put back week after week.

 @{fg shine}Enjoy!@{fg text} :-D


 @{b}SPECIAL EDITION NOTICE@{ub}

 Due to communication breakdown (!) this package wasn't uploaded to
 the Aminet when it was first released, so when I came aware of this
 (Thanks Roman!) this week, I decided to release this @{fg shine}SPECIAL EDITION@{fg text}
 with a couple of extra icons (5 to be precise).
 Sorry for any inconvenience!

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Information" "Information"
@TOC "MAIN"

 All the icons in this package are in 8 colors, 3 bitplanes.

 MagicWB v2.0 have a demon that controls the icons so they have the correct
 colors. So if you use a 16+ color MagicWB, the icon colors will not be
 messed up. This makes MagicWB v2.0 nearly as fast as the standard 4 color
 icons.

 There are many utilities available now that do the same as the MagicWB demon.
 Get hold of one if you aren't a registered MagicWB user.

 Use IconDepth (v1.4), DoIcon (v1.4), OptIcon (ITool201.LhA) or whatever to
 convert your icons to 3 bitplanes, for speed.

 I have saved the ImageDrawers as projects or tools, so I don't have to make
 a dummy file to avoid SwazInfo and other programs to go apeshit when you drop
 the icons in it's field!

@ENDNODE

